data.description: You gotta come see it to believe it! What a bargain. This home doesn't need much to bring it to its heyday. Seller says it was recently remodeled last year but has been neglected since. A little love and some elbow grease and you may have a great home at a great price, if you don't mind waiting for the bank. View of Lake Elsinore from front door/porch. Tax assessor says it's a 3 bedroom 2 bath. It's actually a 2 bedroom 1.5 bath. There is a room that could easily be used as a bedroom next to the other bedrooms but it has no closet so I'm calling it an Office/Den. Wall/window AC's in many of the rooms, Wall heater. On Septic. Large Yard. Hardwood Floors. Windows don't appear to be too old. Unique layout in the sense that front door is upstairs and leads to the bedrooms and bathrooms with an additional backdoor that leads to backyard. There is a downstairs door that enters from carport and into Living room and Kitchen area. Open concept downstairs with some modern touches. No garage, There are a lot of really great things about this house and truly just needs someone to put some love back into it. This property is being offered AS IS. Accuracy of all information, regardless of source, including but not limited to square footage's and lot sizes, is deemed reliable but not guaranteed and should be personally verified through personal inspection by and/or with the appropriate professionals No warranties expressed or implied. Buyer to verify and satisfy on all aspects of the property such as, but not limited to permits, bed/bath count, square footage, legality, etc.
